# Tailwind CSS Configuration for Next.js + Vercel

## Meta
- **Title**: Tailwind CSS Configuration for Next.js + Vercel
- **Description**: Ensure proper Tailwind CSS usage and configuration for SSG landing page
- **Created At**: Jun 10, 2025
- **Last Updated At**: Jun 10, 2025
- **Applies To**:
  - Next.js App Router files (`app/**/*.tsx`)
  - Tailwind config (`tailwind.config.js`)

## Requirements
### All styles must be formulated using Tailwind CSS classes and JIT enabled
- **Priority**: High
- **Correct Example**:
  ```jsx
  className="bg-blue-500 text-white p-6"
  ```
- **Incorrect Example**:
  ```css
  .my-class { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  ```

### Use Next.js `<Image>` component for optimized images
- **Priority**: High
- **Correct Example**:
  ```jsx
  import Image from 'next/image';
  <Image src="/hero.png" alt="Hero" width={1200} height={600} />
  ```
- **Incorrect Example**:
  ```html
  <img src="/hero.png" alt="Hero" />
  ```

